article.headline: Iona 85, Siena 78
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- Steve Burtt scored 30 points and Iona never trailed in an 85-78 win over Siena on Tuesday night. The Gaels (14-3, 8-1 Metro Atlantic Athletic) had the first nine points of the game and built a 38-28 halftime lead. Kojo Mensah and Antoine Jordan each scored 15 points in the second half, but it wasn't enough for the Saints (9-8, 4-5). Mensah finished with 21 points and Jordan with 20. Kenny Jackson's 3-pointer pushed Iona's lead back to eight points with 3 minutes remaining. The Gaels shot 50 percent overall and made all eight of their free throws in the final 1:20 of the game. Kiril Wachsmann added 14 points for Iona, while Jackson had 12 and Ricky Soliver 10. Also in double figures for Siena were David Ryan with 14 points and Kenny Hasbrouck with 11.
